RE: Dating problems (28-11-2012 07:28 PM)Atothetheist Wrote: My girlfriend is wondering if my atheism makes me less emotional, seeing as sometimes I say that emotional appeals do nothing for me. She talked to me about how it needs to stop, and that emotions are important.
She also is hinting that she wants me to buy something, any suggestions?
I think that doubting your own emotions, simply means you do not react to situations purely on emotions. That you step back and reason through things, research, understand and then overcome. Not a bad way to life. In fact I see it as a positive thing.
So I'd explain it to her like that, and that we don't always trust our emotions and thoughts right away.
"Man is an emotional animal, occasionally rational; and through his feelings he can be deceived to his heart's content." - Durant
"Nothing is easier than self-deceit. For what each man wishes, that he also believes to be true." - Demosthenes
Member of the Cult of Reason
The atheist is a man who destroys the imaginary things which afflict the human race, and so leads men back to nature, to experience and to reason.
-Baron d'Holbach-
