RE: Dating problems I agree with fstrat on that, and I also see it as a positive thing, since it means you're less likely to be deceived and make dumb decisions based on emotion; rather, you're likely to think things through calmly and rationally first. But then, I'm a person who is unemotional to a fault (according to others, including ex-boyfriend) so maybe you shouldn't listen to me. ^_^
But I imagine Ato's GF's real problem is she thinks because he isn't influenced by emotion appeal in argument, he somehow can't form emotional attachments to other people, which is not necessarily the case.
